                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="24" value="Shared resource&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;(VPC endpoint/proxy/app target)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;" style="sketch=0;outlineConnect=0;fontColor=#232F3E;gradientColor=none;fillColor=#8C4FFF;strokeColor=#ffffff;dashed=0;verticalLabelPosition=bottom;verticalAlign=top;align=center;html=1;fontSize=14;fontStyle=0;aspect=fixed;shape=mxgraph.aws4.endpoint;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="2460" y="1130" width="60" height="60" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="25" value="&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;Resource&lt;/font&gt;" style="endArrow=classic;html=1;strokeWidth=2.5;strokeColor=#8B0000;rounded=1;fontSize=14;fontColor=#8B0000;" edge="1" parent="1" source="21" target="24">
                    <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="26" value="4" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#2E73B8;strokeColor=none;fontColor=#FFFFFF;fontStyle=1;fontSize=14;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="2375" y="1120" width="26" height="26" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="27" value="&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;Steps&lt;br&gt;(0) DNS: the consumer resolves a custom domain. Because an SN-E creates no automatic Private Hosted Zone, you author a CNAME (or Alias) record in a Route 53 private hosted zone in the Network account, mapping the custom domain to the SN-E generated DNS name; at scale this is automated via EventBridge + Step Functions + Route 53. External / on-premises resolvers reach that record by forwarding the query into AWS through a Route 53 Resolver inbound endpoint; the record returns the SN-E IP.&lt;br&gt;(1) The consumer connects to the SN-E IP over its existing path to AWS (Direct Connect, Site-to-Site VPN, VPC peering, Transit Gateway, or Cloud WAN). A single SN-E reaches all services and resources associated to its service network.&lt;br&gt;(2) The SN-E carries the connection privately over PrivateLink into the Service Network. The Service Network IAM auth policy is still evaluated, so cross-environment isolation holds for SN-E consumers exactly as for SN-A.&lt;br&gt;(3) The Service Network forwards the raw TCP flow to the Resource Gateway for the target Resource Configuration.&lt;br&gt;(4) The Resource Gateway forwards to the shared resource (an interface VPC endpoint, the egress proxy, or an application target). The response returns along the same path.&lt;/font&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FBFBFB;strokeColor=#879196;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=12;spacingTop=10;fontSize=14;fontColor=#232F3E;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="1200" y="1520" width="1400" height="140" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
            </root>
        </mxGraphModel>
    </diagram>
</mxfile>
